node.text:
Part 1- This routine was originally danced to a different song. I wanted to re-shoot this video and make some changes, but the other day just for fun I put “Don’t go yet” by @camila_cabello on top of the video and to my surprise it kind of worked. Not perfectly but enough to make me smile at the happy coincidence. You can definitely see the moments that don’t sync up, but also surprisingly see the moments that work perfectly. 
Come see @hayley.erbert and I dance Live in Las Vegas . Link in bio for tickets ☝🏼🎫
Sept 22nd- Nov 23rd

node.text: I coached @nastialiukin on @dancingabc so it only made sense that she coached me for the Olympics. This video just makes me  laugh. I love this memory. My admiration and respect for Olympic athletes is over flowing. The dedication and sacrifices they endure to be The Best is inspiring. Each year pushing the limits and their abilities to the edge. I feel very fortunate to have had the opportunity to meet and work with  Gold Medalist Olympians who we perceive to be super human. And as impressive as their skills are, getting to know them as human beings was a gift. #olympics

Sometimes I listen to the same thing over and over again until I truly feel the words wash over me, giving me clarity and energy to tackle whatever lies ahead. 
This clip of @thelesbrown always gets me fired up. When all feels lost just remember “ITS NOT OVER UNTIL I WIN”

node.text:
Old footage of me playing Ren McCormack in FOOTLOOSE on the West End in London. 
My first big role, skinny little inexperienced kid giving his All 8 Times a week. My jeans 👖 were soaking wet after every show. I would ring them out and put the damp jeans back on for the second show on Friday’s and Saturday’s. 
I would lose my voice all the time cause I didn’t know how to use it properly. Took me a few months to understand breathe control and proper support. That experience taught me so much including a work ethic that I carry with me into everything I do today. Also, shout out to my boy @giovannispanoofficial #worldtheatreday

This isn’t the first time @celinedion has burst out in song over something I said. 
My first season of DWTS I passed her on the steps and she said “Derek Hough” . I was in shock she knew my name and pulled a “Baby” moment from “Dirty Dancing”. All I could muster up to say was “I’m holding my dance shoes”. 🤦🏼‍♂️ And in true Queen Celine fashion, she started singing (Full Out) 🎼 “Derek is holding his shoes Ah yeah, Derek is holding his shoes, Uh Huh!” And then she danced away as I sat there holding my shoes.
Who knows, now that we’re both performing in Vegas, maybe that Dance might happen :)) 🕺🏼
Get your tickets now 
Link in bio ☝🏼🎫
